{"hash":"9cfdb9e813d598ad0ec52dd1b76789cfbf795114","data":{"post":{"title":"Event bubbling for Dummies","date":"August 20, 2023","content":"<p>Before we can go into what Event bubbling is, we have to make sure that we understand what an <code>Event</code> is.</p>\n<p>An <code>Event</code> is something that happens on a webpage, for example, a user clicking on a button or an error that occurs.</p>\n<p>Events are fired and then handled via an event handler. (Or ignored if we don't have any event handler listing for that Event)</p>\n<h2 id=\"events-in-action\"><a href=\"#events-in-action\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Events in action</h2>\n<p>An example of an event being fired and an event handler looks like this.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;button&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">Click Me</span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/button&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;script&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">document</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">querySelector</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">button</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">)</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">addEventListener</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">click</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">)</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">=&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">console</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">log</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>So what is happening here is the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We search the button via the querySelector</li>\n<li>We attach an event listener</li>\n<li>We <code>console.log</code> the event</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Now let's go into event bubbling.</p>\n<h2 id=\"event-bubbling\"><a href=\"#event-bubbling\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Event bubbling</h2>\n<p>The example above is pretty straightforward, but what happens if we don't attach the event handler to the button directly?</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;button&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">Click Me</span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/button&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;script&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">document</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">querySelector</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">div</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">)</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">addEventListener</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">click</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">)</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">=&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">console</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">log</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>In this case, we attach the event handler to the div that is the <strong>parent</strong> of the button. Even though the event handler\nis not attached to the button, the event handler still gets called.</p>\n<p>This is because the event \"bubbles\" up from the child element to the parent element and so on.</p>\n<p>It is noteworthy that the event will keep \"bubbling up\" after an event handler has already handled it.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;button&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">Click Me</span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/button&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;script&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">document</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">querySelector</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">div</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">)</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">addEventListener</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">click</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">)</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">=&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">console</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">log</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">document</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">querySelector</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">button</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">)</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">addEventListener</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">click</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">)</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">=&gt;</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">console</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">.</span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">log</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">(</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">event</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Both event handlers will be called.</p>\n","tags":[{"title":"JavaScript","path":"/tag/JavaScript/"},{"title":"Frontend","path":"/tag/Frontend/"}]}},"context":{}}